4 A BILL
5 TO BE ENTITLED
6 AN ACT
7
8
9 Relating to Mobile County; to further provide for the
10 office of constable.
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
12 Section 1. (a) In Mobile County, beginning with the
13 terms commencing in 2029, there shall be three constables for
14 each Alabama House of Representatives district with territory
15 in the county, to be elected as provided by law. Each
16 constable shall hold office for four years from the first
17 Monday after the second Tuesday next after his or her election
18 and until his or her successor is elected and qualified.
19 (b) Beginning with the terms commencing in 2029, each
20 constable must be a qualified elector of the district he or
21 she represents to be eligible to perform the duties of the
22 office.
23 Section 2. This act shall become effective January 1,
24 2028, contingent on the enactment of a general law authorizing
25 the alteration of the office of constable by local
26 legislation.
